<div class='row'>
	<div class="col-md-2">
		<p>Here you can edit the menu of your website.</p>
	</div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h3>Sort mode</h3>
        <p>To be able to determine the order of your menu items, you can turn on Sort mode with the button <span class="label label-default">Sort mode is off. Click to turn on</span>. Which sort mode enabled, you can drag and drop the menu items to your liking.</p>
    </div>
	<div class="col-md-3">
        <h3>Hover info</h3>
        <p>To get more info about the item which is linked to a menu item, just hover over the <span class="label label-warning">Module</span> <span class="label label-success">Page</span> or <span class="label label-info">Link</span> tag.</p>
        <p>And when you hover over the name of the menu item, you will see the URL for that menu item.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-4">
        <h3>Quick edit</h3>
        <p>To edit the <b>visibility</b> or <b>access rights</b> for a menu item, you can just click on the visibility or access tags of a menu item to toggle between settings.</p>
        <p><span class="label label-danger">Beware</span> when changing the access right for a menu item linked to a module, you will only determine who will see the item in his menu. It will not limit the access to the module itself!</p>
	</div>
</div>
